missionEventData.data1: Outpost D-34 is now on red alert. After interrogating the Rebel prisoners, we have discovered that their plan was to infiltrate the station disabling all defensive systems and fighter support craft before a Rebel force moved in to capture the station. While we don’t know the Rebel’s current plans, we believe there is a good chance that they will continue with their operation. As a precaution we will be putting all squadrons on constant rotation until help arrives from the Imperial Star Destroyer Hammer and the Nebulon B2 Frigate Fogger.
Sector alert! There are unknown craft entering our area
They're hostile! All Tie Fighters engage.
A second wave of fighters incoming. Engage and destroy!
Three Mugaari Corvettes have just jumped out of hyperspace and are heading for the station. Hold them off until help arrives.
This is the ISD Hammer to all Imperial vessels. Stand clear of the corvettes!
Stay on the look out. Enemy ships could appear at any moment.
Well done Alpha One. The Hammer is now taking over all defensive operations. You can continue patrolling the area or return to base.

missionEventData.data2: The Empire has been dealt a serious blow! The Emperor's secret weapon, the Death Star, has been destroyed. But justice has been swift. Darth Vader, the Emperor's special envoy, crushed the Rebel base on Hoth and now has the Rebels on the run. High Command have issued a warning to all Imperial outposts, be alert for Rebel forces attempting to flee their base on Hoth. Meanwhile, far out on the Outer Rim, the Imperial Tie Fighter pilot, Maarek Steele, begins his patrol...

missionEventData.data3: Thanks to your spirited defense of the platform, Outpost D-34 was able to hold off the Rebel attack. The Hammer will now be continuing its tour of the region, while the Fogger remains to help us maintain order in this sector…
